description: dotscope — Python module (23 files)
includes:
  - dotscope/
excludes:
  - dotscope/__pycache__/
  - "*.pyc"
context: |
  dotscope — Directory-scoped context boundaries for AI coding agents.
  Documentation absorber: extract architectural knowledge from existing docs.
  
  Scans for and extracts knowledge from:
  - README.md, ARCHITECTURE.md, CONTRIBUTING.md
  - Docstrings (module-level and class-level)
  - Inline comments with signals: NOTE, HACK, TODO, WARNING, FIXME, XXX, IMPORTANT
  - Type hints and function signatures (contract-like information)
  
  AST-powered code analysis. Structural understanding of source files.
  
  Python: uses stdlib `ast` module — zero dependencies.
  JS/TS: enhanced regex (no heavy AST dep for v1).
  Go: enhanced regex.
  
  Scope backtesting: validate generated scopes against actual git history.
  
  Replays recent commits and measures whether each scope's includes would have
  covered the files that were actually changed. Self-corrects by suggesting
  missing includes.
  
  Token budgeting: rank files, fill to budget, progressive loading.
  
  Context is always included first. Then files are ranked and loaded
  until the budget is exhausted.
  
  CLI entry point for dotscope.
  Scope composition algebra.
  
  Supports expressions like:
      auth+payments     — merge (union of files, concatenate context)
      auth-tests        — subtract (remove files matching subtracted scope)
      auth&api          — intersect (only files in both)
      auth@context      — modifier (context only, no files)
  
  Operators bind left-to-right, no precedence. @ is a suffix modifier.
  
  Shared constants — single source of truth for all modules.
  INVARIANT: s
  ## Recent Changes
  - Initial release: dotscope v0.1.0
  This module is used by: tests
  Changes here may affect downstream consumers.
related:
  - tests/.scope
tags:
  - dotscope
tokens_estimate: 42229
